### Counting Word Occurrences in a Text File (C++)  
#### Problem Statement  
- Read a text file line by line  
- Count the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file  
#### Solution  
- Open the file for reading  
- Use a `std::string` variable to store each line  
- Use `std::istringstream` to split the line into words  
- Use a `std::map` to store the word and its count  
- Iterate through the words and increment the count for each occurrence  
- Print the word and its count  
#### Code  
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
#include <sstream>
#include <map>

int main() {
  std::string word;  // Word to search for
  std::cout << "Enter the word to search for: ";
  std::cin >> word;

  std::ifstream file("text_file.txt");  // Replace with your file name

  std::map<std::string, int> word_counts;  // Map to store word and count

  if (file.is_open()) {
    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(file, line)) {
      std::istringstream iss(line);
      std::string word;
      while (iss >> word) {
        if (word == word) {
          ++word_counts[word];
        }
      }
    }
    file.close();
  } else {
    std::cerr << "Error opening file" << std::endl;
    return 1;
  }

  for (const auto& entry : word_counts) {
    std::cout << entry.first << ": " << entry.second << std::endl;
  }

  return 0;
}
```
